The article discusses how several companies are benefiting from the recent tax reform implemented by President Trump. Some of the companies mentioned include Home Depot, Pfizer, FedEx, American Family Insurance, Town Bank, BMO Harris Bank, Dynamic Fasteners, The Hammock Source, and Ecolab. These companies are giving bonuses to their employees, raising wages, increasing investments, and making contributions to their charitable foundations. The tax reform has resulted in increased business optimism and confidence, leading to plans for hiring more workers and investing in company growth.